rmk: +10 gain applied to this recording of a Wood Sandpiper migrating over a suburban garden at night. "Wood Sandpipers show only limited variation in their flight calls, which are the same by day or by night. Fortunately, the pi-pe call given by lone migrants, which can be regarded as their default flight call, is not difficult to identify. Single nocturnal migrants always give this call. A brief, high pitched, descending series of short, clearly articulated whistles. Each whistle shaped like an inverted capital letter ‘J’. Normally two whistles but 1 to 4 are not unusual. Frequency range 2.2 - 5.2 KHz."Sound Approach
